The paper also deals with the concepts of recurrence and transience, which are related to the study of Markov chains, and hence the paper may also belong to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category. The study of complete graphs and the asymptotic behavior of random walks suggests that the paper may belong to the Graph Theory (cs.GT) sub-category. The paper also deals with the notion of entropy and information theory, which suggests that it may belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses potential applications of random walks, which suggests that it may also belong to the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-category.
